1. memr
sudo python3 ./memr.py -p /dev/ttyACM1 -a 20000100 -b 921600
or 
sudo python3 ./memr.py -p /dev/ttyACM1 -a 20000100 -b 230400


For example:
klinschen@memryx-E500-G9-WS760T:~/accton_1225$ sudo python3 ./memr.py -p /dev/ttyACM1 -a 20000100 -b 921600
0x20000100 : 0x00000512

The value 0x512 means:

bits[8:7] = 0x2  ->> pcie boot
2'b00 : QSPI
2'b01 : USB
2'b10 : PCIe
2'b11 : UART

bits[6:4] = 0x1  ->> mode2

3'b000 : Mode 1 - 1st Chip - USB Host / Chained
3'b001 : Mode 2 - 1st Chip - PCIe Host / Chained
3'b010 : Mode 3 - Single Chip - PCIe Host
3'b011 : Mode 4 - 1st Chip - USB & PCIe Host / Chained
3'b100 : Mode 5 - Last Chip
3'b101 : Mode 6 - Single Chip - USB Host
3'b110 : Mode 7 - Leagcy USB
3'b111 : Mode 8 -1st Chip - PCIe Host / Chained

2. Update Flash:

sudo python3 uart_WrLodaer.py -p /dev/ttyACM1 -b 230400 -f EyeSurf.bin -w uart_WrLodaer.raw